posts.message: I don't know if you have heard about this or not, but there is an amazing initative in the open source community to bring the kindness back to the opensource community by helping first timers make their first PR (Pull Request). It's all explained here it won't matter if you've been coding for 10 years or just started a month ago. It is worth mentioning that this initiative is by Scott Hansleman and Kent Dodds.
posts.caption: firsttimersonly.com
posts.description: Contributing to open source for the first time can be scary and a little overwhelming. Perhaps you're a Code Newbie or maybe you've been coding for a while but haven't found a project you felt comfortable contributing to.
